HEADWORD: Glaucophane
<hw>Glau"co*phane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>glayko`s</grk> silvery, gray + <grk>fai`nesqai</grk> to
appear.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a dark bluish color,
related to amphibole. It is characteristic of certain crystalline
rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

